	<main>
		<p>A lexer converts an input stream of characters into a sequence of tokens, including the location and nature of the token.</p>
		
		<p>Tokens can then be used by a parser to build a program tree. If there is an error (e.g. an unexpected/invalid sequence of tokens), the location information can be used to formulate a useful error message.</p>
		
